ugin/provider/agentcube.py` skeleton\n146:   - Purpose: Provider class for credential validation\n147:   - Import: `from dify_plugin import ToolProvider`, `from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError`, `from typing import Any`\n148:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n149:   - Verification: `python -c \"import ast; ast.parse(open('integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py').read())\"`\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T5.2**: Define `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` class\n152:   - Purpose: Provider class inheriting from ToolProvider\n153:   - Class: `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):`\n154:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n155:   - Verification: `grep \"class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider\" integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n156: \n157: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `_validate_credentials` method\n158:   - Purpose: Credential validation hook\n159:   - Signature: `def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:`\n160:   - Raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on failure\n161:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n162:   - Verification: `grep \"_validate_credentials\" integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement credential validation logic\n165:   - Purpose: Validate router_url and workload_manager_url presence\n166:   - Check: `credentials.get(\"router_url\")` and `credentials.get(\"workload_manager_url\")` non-empty\n167:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n168:   - Verification: `grep \"router_url\" integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n169: \n170: ### Phase 6: Tool Schema (ST-6)\n171: \n172: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n173:   - Purpose: Tool parameter schema definition\n174:   - Fields: `identity.name: agentcube-code-interpreter`, `identity.author: agentcube`\n175:   - Fi